{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":500,"text":"So my freshman year of college"},{"time":1944,"text":"I signed up for an internship in the housing unit"},{"time":4694,"text":"at Greater Boston Legal Services."},{"time":6894,"text":"Showed up the first day"},{"time":8547,"text":"ready to make coffee and photocopies,"},{"time":10863,"text":"but was paired with this righteous, deeply inspired attorney"},{"time":15445,"text":"named Jeff Purcell,"},{"time":16914,"text":"who thrust me onto the front lines"},{"time":19379,"text":"from the very first day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21379,"text":"And over the course of nine months"},{"time":23144,"text":"I had the chance"},{"time":24157,"text":"to have dozens of conversations"},{"time":25929,"text":"with low-income families in Boston"},{"time":28713,"text":"who would come in presenting with housing issues,"},{"time":31829,"text":"but always had an underlying health issue."},{"time":35113,"text":"So I had a client who came in,"},{"time":37345,"text":"about to be evicted because he hasn't paid his rent."},{"time":39663,"text":"But he hasn't paid his rent, of course,"},{"time":41951,"text":"because he's paying for his HIV medication"},{"time":44445,"text":"and just can't afford both."},{"time":46645,"text":"We had moms who would come in,"},{"time":47996,"text":"daughter has asthma,"},{"time":49379,"text":"wakes up covered in cockroaches every morning."},{"time":52264,"text":"And one of our litigation strategies"},{"time":54237,"text":"was actually to send me into the home of these clients"},{"time":57012,"text":"with these large glass bottles."},{"time":59145,"text":"And I would collect the cockroaches,"},{"time":61145,"text":"hot glue-gun them to this poster board"},{"time":64163,"text":"that we'd bring to court for our cases."},{"time":66195,"text":"And we always won"},{"time":67473,"text":"because the judges were just so grossed out."},{"time":70195,"text":"Far more effective, I have to say,"},{"time":72344,"text":"than anything I later learned in law school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75195,"text":"But over the course of these nine months,"},{"time":77745,"text":"I grew frustrated with feeling"},{"time":79596,"text":"like we were intervening too far downstream"},{"time":82562,"text":"in the lives of our clients --"},{"time":85079,"text":"that by the time they came to us,"},{"time":86611,"text":"they were already in crisis."},{"time":88779,"text":"And at the end of my freshman year of college,"},{"time":91595,"text":"I read an article about the work"},{"time":93279,"text":"that Dr. Barry Zuckerman was doing"},{"time":95061,"text":"as Chair of Pediatrics"},{"time":97197,"text":"at Boston Medical Center."},{"time":98597,"text":"And his first hire was a legal services attorney"},{"time":101664,"text":"to represent the patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103546,"text":"So I called Barry,"},{"time":105061,"text":"and with his blessing, in October 1995"},{"time":107664,"text":"walked into the waiting room"},{"time":109729,"text":"of the pediatrics clinic at Boston Medical Center."},{"time":112595,"text":"I'll never forget,"},{"time":113928,"text":"the TVs played this endless reel of cartoons."},{"time":116812,"text":"And the exhaustion of mothers"},{"time":119746,"text":"who had taken two, three, sometimes four buses"},{"time":123278,"text":"to bring their child to the doctor"},{"time":125210,"text":"was just palpable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127094,"text":"The doctors, it seemed,"},{"time":128342,"text":"never really had enough time for all the patients,"},{"time":129861,"text":"try as they might."},{"time":131111,"text":"And over the course of six months,"},{"time":132329,"text":"I would corner them in the hallway"},{"time":134010,"text":"and ask them a sort of naive but fundamental question:"},{"time":137911,"text":"\"If you had unlimited resources,"},{"time":140396,"text":"what's the one thing you would give your patients?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":143711,"text":"And I heard the same story again and again,"},{"time":146411,"text":"a story we've heard hundreds of times since then."},{"time":149361,"text":"They said, \"Every day we have patients that come into the clinic --"},{"time":152926,"text":"child has an ear infection,"},{"time":154627,"text":"I prescribe antibiotics."},{"time":156560,"text":"But the real issue is there's no food at home."},{"time":159393,"text":"The real issue"},{"time":160894,"text":"is that child is living with 12 other people"},{"time":163128,"text":"in a two-bedroom apartment."},{"time":164626,"text":"And I don't even ask about those issues"},{"time":166476,"text":"because there's nothing I can do."},{"time":169227,"text":"I have 13 minutes with each patient."},{"time":171065,"text":"Patients are piling up in the clinic waiting room."},{"time":173634,"text":"I have no idea where the nearest food pantry is."},{"time":176319,"text":"And I don't even have any help.\""},{"time":178667,"text":"In that clinic, even today,"},{"time":179867,"text":"there are two social workers"},{"time":181553,"text":"for 24,000 pediatric patients,"},{"time":184284,"text":"which is better than a lot of the clinics out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187136,"text":"So Health Leads was born of these conversations --"},{"time":190167,"text":"a simple model"},{"time":191351,"text":"where doctors and nurses"},{"time":192866,"text":"can prescribe nutritious food,"},{"time":195084,"text":"heat in the winter"},{"time":196386,"text":"and other basic resources for their patients"},{"time":198968,"text":"the same way they prescribe medication."},{"time":201519,"text":"Patients then take their prescriptions"},{"time":203500,"text":"to our desk in the clinic waiting room"},{"time":205967,"text":"where we have a core of well-trained college student advocates"},{"time":209784,"text":"who work side by side with these families"},{"time":212236,"text":"to connect them out"},{"time":213535,"text":"to the existing landscape of community resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216751,"text":"So we began with a card table in the clinic waiting room --"},{"time":220300,"text":"totally lemonade stand style."},{"time":222450,"text":"But today we have a thousand college student advocates"},{"time":225770,"text":"who are working to connect nearly 9,000 patients and their families"},{"time":230070,"text":"with the resources that they need to be healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233271,"text":"So 18 months ago"},{"time":234787,"text":"I got this email that changed my life."},{"time":237572,"text":"And the email was from Dr. Jack Geiger,"},{"time":239987,"text":"who had written to congratulate me on Health Leads"},{"time":242971,"text":"and to share, as he said,"},{"time":244270,"text":"a bit of historical context."},{"time":246906,"text":"In 1965 Dr. Geiger founded"},{"time":249856,"text":"one of the first two community health centers in this country,"},{"time":252870,"text":"in a brutally poor area in the Mississippi Delta."},{"time":256021,"text":"And so many of his patients came in"},{"time":258537,"text":"presenting with malnutrition"},{"time":260687,"text":"that be began prescribing food for them."},{"time":263171,"text":"And they would take these prescriptions to the local supermarket,"},{"time":266422,"text":"which would fill them"},{"time":267520,"text":"and then charge the pharmacy budget of the clinic."},{"time":270338,"text":"And when the Office of Economic Opportunity in Washington, D.C. --"},{"time":273221,"text":"which was funding Geiger's clinic --"},{"time":275056,"text":"found out about this,"},{"time":276255,"text":"they were furious."},{"time":277455,"text":"And they sent this bureaucrat down"},{"time":279204,"text":"to tell Geiger that he was expected to use their dollars"},{"time":282155,"text":"for medical care --"},{"time":283621,"text":"to which Geiger famously and logically responded,"},{"time":287021,"text":"\"The last time I checked my textbooks,"},{"time":289446,"text":"the specific therapy for malnutrition was food.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":293805,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295089,"text":"So when I got this email from Dr. Geiger,"},{"time":297788,"text":"I knew I was supposed to be proud"},{"time":300154,"text":"to be part of this history."},{"time":301821,"text":"But the truth is"},{"time":303037,"text":"I was devastated."},{"time":305029,"text":"Here we are,"},{"time":306370,"text":"45 years after Geiger has prescribed food for his patients,"},{"time":310355,"text":"and I have doctors telling me,"},{"time":312370,"text":"\"On those issues, we practice a 'don't ask, don't tell' policy.\""},{"time":316437,"text":"Forty-five years after Geiger,"},{"time":318870,"text":"Health Leads has to reinvent"},{"time":320421,"text":"the prescription for basic resources."},{"time":323256,"text":"So I have spent hours upon hours"},{"time":326421,"text":"trying to make sense of this weird Groundhog Day."},{"time":329755,"text":"How is it that if for decades"},{"time":332289,"text":"we had a pretty straightforward tool for keeping patients,"},{"time":335058,"text":"and especially low-income patients, healthy,"},{"time":337655,"text":"that we didn't use it?"},{"time":339556,"text":"If we know what it takes to have a healthcare system"},{"time":342655,"text":"rather than a sick-care system,"},{"time":345154,"text":"why don't we just do it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347187,"text":"These questions, in my mind,"},{"time":349421,"text":"are not hard because the answers are complicated,"},{"time":352487,"text":"they are hard because they require that we be honest with ourselves."},{"time":357621,"text":"My belief is that it's almost too painful"},{"time":360721,"text":"to articulate our aspirations for our healthcare system,"},{"time":363950,"text":"or even admit that we have any at all."},{"time":366688,"text":"Because if we did,"},{"time":367855,"text":"they would be so removed"},{"time":369471,"text":"from our current reality."},{"time":371657,"text":"But that doesn't change my belief"},{"time":374620,"text":"that all of us, deep inside,"},{"time":377538,"text":"here in this room and across this country,"},{"time":381105,"text":"share a similar set of desires."},{"time":384021,"text":"That if we are honest with ourselves"},{"time":386154,"text":"and listen quietly,"},{"time":388455,"text":"that we all harbor"},{"time":390271,"text":"one fiercely held aspiration for our healthcare:"},{"time":394471,"text":"that it keep us healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396571,"text":"This aspiration that our healthcare keep us healthy"},{"time":399888,"text":"is an enormously powerful one."},{"time":402288,"text":"And the way I think about this"},{"time":404905,"text":"is that healthcare is like any other system."},{"time":407089,"text":"It's just a set of choices that people make."},{"time":409655,"text":"What if we decided"},{"time":411456,"text":"to make a different set of choices?"},{"time":413872,"text":"What if we decided to take all the parts of healthcare"},{"time":416904,"text":"that have drifted away from us"},{"time":418706,"text":"and stand firm and say, \"No."},{"time":421172,"text":"These things are ours."},{"time":423139,"text":"They will be used for our purposes."},{"time":425138,"text":"They will be used to realize"},{"time":427162,"text":"our aspiration\"?"},{"time":429093,"text":"What if everything we needed"},{"time":430843,"text":"to realize our aspiration for healthcare"},{"time":432988,"text":"was right there in front of us"},{"time":434571,"text":"just waiting to be claimed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436455,"text":"So that's where Health Leads began."},{"time":438505,"text":"We started with the prescription pad --"},{"time":440189,"text":"a very ordinary piece of paper --"},{"time":442588,"text":"and we asked, not what do patients need to get healthy --"},{"time":446556,"text":"antibiotics, an inhaler, medication --"},{"time":449574,"text":"but what do patients need to be healthy,"},{"time":452357,"text":"to not get sick in the first place?"},{"time":454904,"text":"And we chose to use the prescription"},{"time":456755,"text":"for that purpose."},{"time":458537,"text":"So just a few miles from here"},{"time":459739,"text":"at Children's National Medical Center,"},{"time":461523,"text":"when patients come into the doctor's office,"},{"time":463789,"text":"they're asked a few questions."},{"time":465474,"text":"They're asked, \"Are you running out of food at the end of the month?"},{"time":468138,"text":"Do you have safe housing?\""},{"time":469704,"text":"And when the doctor begins the visit,"},{"time":471773,"text":"she knows height, weight, is there food at home,"},{"time":474606,"text":"is the family living in a shelter."},{"time":476222,"text":"And that not only leads to a better set of clinical choices,"},{"time":479106,"text":"but the doctor can also prescribe those resources for the patient,"},{"time":483156,"text":"using Health Leads like any other sub-specialty referral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486822,"text":"The problem is,"},{"time":489055,"text":"once you get a taste of what it's like"},{"time":491254,"text":"to realize your aspiration for healthcare,"},{"time":493489,"text":"you want more."},{"time":495007,"text":"So we thought,"},{"time":495770,"text":"if we can get individual doctors"},{"time":497371,"text":"to prescribe these basic resources for their patients,"},{"time":500588,"text":"could we get an entire healthcare system"},{"time":503305,"text":"to shift its presumption?"},{"time":506057,"text":"And we gave it a shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507304,"text":"So now at Harlem Hospital Center"},{"time":508739,"text":"when patients come in with an elevated body mass index,"},{"time":512525,"text":"the electronic medical record"},{"time":514389,"text":"automatically generates a prescription for Health Leads."},{"time":518189,"text":"And our volunteers can then work with them"},{"time":519655,"text":"to connect patients to healthy food and excercise programs"},{"time":522872,"text":"in their communities."},{"time":524304,"text":"We've created a presumption"},{"time":525438,"text":"that if you're a patient at that hospital"},{"time":527005,"text":"with an elevated BMI,"},{"time":528555,"text":"the four walls of the doctor's office"},{"time":530789,"text":"probably aren't going to give you everything"},{"time":532641,"text":"you need to be healthy."},{"time":533823,"text":"You need more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535223,"text":"So on the one hand,"},{"time":535904,"text":"this is just a basic recoding"},{"time":537601,"text":"of the electronic medical record."},{"time":539306,"text":"And on the other hand,"},{"time":541024,"text":"it's a radical transformation"},{"time":542673,"text":"of the electronic medical record"},{"time":544841,"text":"from a static repository of diagnostic information"},{"time":548723,"text":"to a health promotion tool."},{"time":551557,"text":"In the private sector,"},{"time":552674,"text":"when you squeeze that kind of additional value"},{"time":555294,"text":"out of a fixed-cost investment,"},{"time":557041,"text":"it's called a billion-dollar company."},{"time":559641,"text":"But in my world,"},{"time":561022,"text":"it's called reduced obesity and diabetes."},{"time":564423,"text":"It's called healthcare --"},{"time":566306,"text":"a system where doctors can prescribe solutions"},{"time":569289,"text":"to improve health,"},{"time":570839,"text":"not just manage disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572988,"text":"Same thing in the clinic waiting room."},{"time":574522,"text":"So every day in this country"},{"time":576139,"text":"three million patients"},{"time":577639,"text":"pass through about 150,000 clinic waiting rooms in this country."},{"time":582144,"text":"And what do they do when they're there?"},{"time":584117,"text":"They sit, they watch the goldfish in the fish tank,"},{"time":587567,"text":"they read extremely old copies"},{"time":590050,"text":"of Good Housekeeping magazine."},{"time":592333,"text":"But mostly we all just sit there forever, waiting."},{"time":595566,"text":"How did we get here"},{"time":596917,"text":"where we devote hundreds of acres and thousands of hours"},{"time":600266,"text":"to waiting?"},{"time":602049,"text":"What if we had a waiting room"},{"time":603266,"text":"where you don't just sit when you're sick,"},{"time":605367,"text":"but where you go to get healthy."},{"time":607233,"text":"If airports can become shopping malls"},{"time":609750,"text":"and McDonald's can become playgrounds,"},{"time":612716,"text":"surely we can reinvent the clinic waiting room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616149,"text":"And that's what Health Leads has tried to do,"},{"time":618183,"text":"to reclaim that real estate and that time"},{"time":620466,"text":"and to use it as a gateway"},{"time":621898,"text":"to connect patients"},{"time":622950,"text":"to the resources they need to be healthy."},{"time":625717,"text":"So it's a brutal winter in the Northeast,"},{"time":627233,"text":"your kid has asthma, your heat just got turned off,"},{"time":629700,"text":"and of course you're in the waiting room of the ER,"},{"time":631867,"text":"because the cold air triggered your child's asthma."},{"time":634399,"text":"But what if instead of waiting for hours anxiously,"},{"time":637316,"text":"the waiting room became the place"},{"time":639516,"text":"where Health Leads turned your heat back on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"And of course all of this requires"},{"time":643618,"text":"a broader workforce."},{"time":645566,"text":"But if we're creative, we already have that too."},{"time":648733,"text":"We know that our doctors and nurses"},{"time":651119,"text":"and even social workers"},{"time":652466,"text":"aren't enough,"},{"time":653934,"text":"that the ticking minutes of health care"},{"time":655583,"text":"are too constraining."},{"time":657001,"text":"Health just takes more time."},{"time":659050,"text":"It requires a non-clinical army"},{"time":661849,"text":"of community health workers and case managers"},{"time":664533,"text":"and many others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666149,"text":"What if a small part of that next healthcare workforce"},{"time":669299,"text":"were the 11 million college students in this country?"},{"time":673000,"text":"Unencumbered by clinical responsibilities,"},{"time":675766,"text":"unwilling to take no for an answer"},{"time":678368,"text":"from those bureaucracies"},{"time":679950,"text":"that tend to crush patients,"},{"time":681883,"text":"and with an unparalleled ability"},{"time":683833,"text":"for information retrieval"},{"time":685285,"text":"honed through years of using Google."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688266,"text":"Now lest you think it improbable"},{"time":690799,"text":"that a college volunteer"},{"time":692416,"text":"can make this kind of commitment,"},{"time":694199,"text":"I have two words for you:"},{"time":695766,"text":"March Madness."},{"time":698117,"text":"The average NCAA Division I men's basketball player"},{"time":702084,"text":"dedicates 39 hours a week to his sport."},{"time":705349,"text":"Now we may think that's good or bad,"},{"time":707501,"text":"but in either case it's real."},{"time":710183,"text":"And Health Leads is based on the presumption"},{"time":712368,"text":"that for too long"},{"time":713750,"text":"we have asked too little of our college students"},{"time":716300,"text":"when it comes to real impact in vulnerable communities."},{"time":720065,"text":"College sports teams say,"},{"time":721418,"text":"\"We're going to take dozens of hours"},{"time":723483,"text":"at some field across campus at some ungodly hour of the morning"},{"time":727367,"text":"and we're going to measure your performance, and your team's performance,"},{"time":730183,"text":"and if you don't measure up or you don't show up,"},{"time":732349,"text":"we're going to cut you off the team."},{"time":733799,"text":"But we'll make huge investments"},{"time":735687,"text":"in your training and development,"},{"time":736899,"text":"and we'll give you an extraordinary community of peers.\""},{"time":740317,"text":"And people line up out the door"},{"time":742132,"text":"just for the chance to be part of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744917,"text":"So our feeling is,"},{"time":746134,"text":"if it's good enough for the rugby team,"},{"time":747617,"text":"it's good enough for health and poverty."},{"time":749732,"text":"Health Leads too recruits competitively,"},{"time":753000,"text":"trains intensively,"},{"time":754481,"text":"coaches professionally,"},{"time":756450,"text":"demands significant time,"},{"time":758399,"text":"builds a cohesive team"},{"time":759766,"text":"and measures results --"},{"time":761250,"text":"a kind of Teach for America for healthcare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763933,"text":"Now in the top 10 cities in the U.S."},{"time":766033,"text":"with the largest number of Medicaid patients,"},{"time":768352,"text":"each of those has at least 20,000 college students."},{"time":771566,"text":"New York alone has half a million college students."},{"time":774767,"text":"And this isn't just a sort of short-term workforce"},{"time":777816,"text":"to connect patients to basic resources,"},{"time":780066,"text":"it's a next generation healthcare leadership pipeline"},{"time":783667,"text":"who've spent two, three, four years"},{"time":786117,"text":"in the clinic waiting room"},{"time":787618,"text":"talking to patients about their most basic health needs."},{"time":791602,"text":"And they leave with the conviction,"},{"time":793351,"text":"the ability and the efficacy"},{"time":795183,"text":"to realize our most basic aspirations for health care."},{"time":798966,"text":"And the thing is, there's thousands of these folks already out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801984,"text":"So Mia Lozada is Chief Resident of Internal Medicine"},{"time":805801,"text":"at UCSF Medical Center,"},{"time":807216,"text":"but for three years as an undergraduate"},{"time":809549,"text":"she was a Health Leads volunteer"},{"time":811182,"text":"in the clinic waiting room at Boston Medical Center."},{"time":814184,"text":"Mia says, \"When my classmates write a prescription,"},{"time":817899,"text":"they think their work is done."},{"time":819917,"text":"When I write a prescription,"},{"time":821633,"text":"I think, can the family read the prescription?"},{"time":823900,"text":"Do they have transportation to the pharmacy?"},{"time":826083,"text":"Do they have food to take with the prescription?"},{"time":828533,"text":"Do they have insurance to fill the prescription?"},{"time":830783,"text":"Those are the questions I learned at Health Leads,"},{"time":833466,"text":"not in medical school.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":835216,"text":"Now none of these solutions --"},{"time":837200,"text":"the prescription pad, the electronic medical record,"},{"time":840170,"text":"the waiting room,"},{"time":841317,"text":"the army of college students --"},{"time":842485,"text":"are perfect."},{"time":843668,"text":"But they are ours for the taking --"},{"time":846168,"text":"simple examples"},{"time":847500,"text":"of the vast under-utilized healthcare resources"},{"time":851001,"text":"that, if we reclaimed and redeployed,"},{"time":853916,"text":"could realize our most basic aspiration"},{"time":857333,"text":"of healthcare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859117,"text":"So I had been at Legal Services for about nine months"},{"time":862333,"text":"when this idea of Health Leads started percolating in my mind."},{"time":865066,"text":"And I knew I had to tell Jeff Purcell, my attorney,"},{"time":868000,"text":"that I needed to leave."},{"time":869419,"text":"And I was so nervous,"},{"time":870382,"text":"because I thought he was going to be disappointed in me"},{"time":872916,"text":"for abandoning our clients for some crazy idea."},{"time":875966,"text":"And I sat down with him and I said,"},{"time":877950,"text":"\"Jeff, I have this idea"},{"time":879833,"text":"that we could mobilize college students"},{"time":882252,"text":"to address patients' most basic health needs.\""},{"time":885186,"text":"And I'll be honest,"},{"time":886767,"text":"all I wanted was for him to not be angry at me."},{"time":890066,"text":"But he said this,"},{"time":891533,"text":"\"Rebecca, when you have a vision,"},{"time":894881,"text":"you have an obligation to realize that vision."},{"time":898732,"text":"You must pursue that vision.\""},{"time":901833,"text":"And I have to say, I was like \"Whoa."},{"time":905099,"text":"That's a lot of pressure.\""},{"time":907116,"text":"I just wanted a blessing,"},{"time":908515,"text":"I didn't want some kind of mandate."},{"time":910066,"text":"But the truth is"},{"time":911633,"text":"I've spent every waking minute nearly since then"},{"time":914416,"text":"chasing that vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916200,"text":"I believe that we all have a vision"},{"time":919382,"text":"for healthcare in this country."},{"time":921283,"text":"I believe that at the end of the day"},{"time":923482,"text":"when we measure our healthcare,"},{"time":925316,"text":"it will not be by the diseases cured,"},{"time":928132,"text":"but by the diseases prevented."},{"time":930650,"text":"It will not be by the excellence of our technologies"},{"time":933667,"text":"or the sophistication of our specialists,"},{"time":936167,"text":"but by how rarely we needed them."},{"time":938966,"text":"And most of all,"},{"time":940450,"text":"I believe that when we measure healthcare,"},{"time":942967,"text":"it will be, not by what the system was,"},{"time":945650,"text":"but by what we chose it to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948416,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949483,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":959733,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961008,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}